The main name, Nile, the river has below the confluence with the largest tributary of the Blue Nile. Three tributaries of the White Nile have names associated with color: Sobat (from Arab. Bahr-el-Asfar - yellow river), Blue Nile (from Arabic. Bahr-el -Azraq - blue river), Atbara (arab. Bahr-el-Aswad - black river) - the right tributary below Khartoum.